    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beans are slightly softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>creamy Dijon stock </strong>to the pan and top with the <strong>chopped smoked basa </strong>and a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 5 min or until your fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>smoked basa with creamy cannellini beans</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
